headline.main: STIMSON CHARGES FINNS HAMPER AID; Secretary Asserts They Are Being 'Used by Germans' to Injure Democracies

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Nov. 25 -- The Administration today served notice on Finland that her war against Russia, with the consequent threat to the Murmansk-Moscow supply line, was directly "harmful to the interests of the United States."
abstract: War Sec Stimson and Maj Gen J H Burns charge Finns action harmful to U S interest; urge war end; statement texts
